Reviews.Title: Extremely slow computer
Reviews.Author: Alex Paradis
Reviews.Content: worked great for about 3 months then got slow and its not a virus I downloaded Macfee the top of the line online sucurity.  In the past 3 months I renstaled vista still runs crappy I feel that 400 dollars is too much and if it was selling for 100 you could consider it (1 GB not 2 GB RAM)

Reviews.Title: Breaks in year
Reviews.Author: Carbine Fox
Reviews.Content: There is design flaw in this computer which causes the solder between the motherboard and graphics card to go bad. Like the others mine went bad in a year of moderate use. Had it repaired twice, once by HP, once by and independent company and has failed again shortly after both. I will no longer be buying HP products nor will I be able to recommend them to friends and family. This coming from someone who once avidly encouraged people to buy HP.

Reviews.Title: didn't last long
Reviews.Author: CJbooks
Reviews.Content: Had the laptop less than a year, The graphic card broke after a few months. Not too happy with Hp.

Reviews.Title: Not what I expected
Reviews.Author: tobbooks.
Reviews.Content: We had two of these computers. The one only lasted 1 year until the mother board burned out, and the second one only lasted 2.5 years because the graphic card broke. Not to reliable and built very cheaply.

Reviews.Title: Not all HP's are bad.....
Reviews.Author: B. Mason
Reviews.Content: This model was my 2nd laptop. I never had any issues with it. I bought mine from Office Max for around$720 with tax in 2005. The only problem I've had out of it is when I.....put a pen on the keyboard near thescreen and foolishly closed it without thinking; cracking the screen. I've taken it apart and depending onprice, I might replace it. I own a Toshiba Satelite and another HP dv6 series bought almost two years ago.In total, I have owned three HP laptops.To make laptops more affordable some parts are made with plastic or other materials which degrade when hot.NO laptop fan will cool it efficiently and require laptop users to need a good laptop fan/cooler. There are waysto circumvent the shortcomings in manufacturing when computer companies do this. I replaced the power jack/porton the Toshiba with a sturdier model which cost $2.99 and about 2 hours labor myself.NO DUCT TAPE INVOLVED.It sucks that many people have had bad experiences with HP. Everyone has their own preferences and I for onehave had great ones with HP. This model is best for a desktop replacement WITH a good laptop cooler.

Reviews.Title: never have had a problem
Reviews.Author: John C. Brewer
Reviews.Content: my hp dv9000 has ran great for 3 years now and it is loaded to the gills with power and speed for an older laptop it has 4gb of memory a digital tv tuner remote control and a blue ray player that I use to drive my 55 inch tv with and it does that very well. I use it as a dvr too. The battery is my only real issue it only holds charge for about an hour or so now so I think I will buy a new battery soon. these laptops do overheat if you dont use a cooling fan underneath them the bottom of the machine just dosent have enough space to circulate any air under its huge baseplate so prolonged use is limited to about an hour if you dont provide a usb cooling device underneath it. once you address that issue it will run true and cool without a hitch. I can only guess that a lot of people have let their laptops fry themselves out rather than spend the 20 dollars on a cooling pad. This computer blows any other laptop I have ever used before out of the water.

Reviews.Title: Tired of HP overheating
Reviews.Author: Joshua J. Danziger
Reviews.Content: Ok, this computer has possessed little to no problems until about 6 months ago. It was purchased in 2008 so it is 4 years old, but I have a Sony Vaio that I purchased back in 2004 which is still being used and works fine, just a little slow compared to today's computers.A minor problem was that the DVD rom drive physically broke, the spinner that holds onto the cd broke off. So guess what, it became useless. After spending more money then I should have for another one, the monitor stopped working. And even when plugging in an external monitor it still did not work. But I could hear the sound of it turning on and making the Window's entrance theme music. So I know the computer is working, just not the graphics card.When looking inside, hp used a small piece of copper to cool BOTH the graphics card and the processor. And guess what, there wasn't even any thermal paste to help with the heat. Wow, HP got so lazy when it came to designing this smartly. The fan was clogged with gunk too. But that happens to any computer.For the cost of the newer HP products, you can find a much more reliable computer for the same price. Read reviews, don't base your purchases off the past. Things change, and HP changed for the worse. I also have overheating problems with the graphics card and processor with their slimelines too. Way to go HP, just like Dell, started off good, then went down the toilet.

Reviews.Title: The worst laptop I ever had...
Reviews.Author: 73r
Reviews.Content: I bought this laptop 3 years ago in the states, then I came back to my country and since the second month I had this laptop It gave me too much problems. First the video card got overheated every time I ran AutoCad 2004 for half n hour... Then when I was watching some videos on youtube it crashes and turn off, the same thing happened when I was for more than 2 hours playing any game, even worms for example. So, Im an electronical engineere and after going 4 times to the HP custome service to ask for a solution to the problem and recieveng the same answer "sorry, the amd prossesor has than problem", I open the laptop, and HP was liyng cause the real problem whas the awfull architectonical design with just 1 fan for the whole electrinical parts, and so the AMD prossesor and the video card got to hot that for security the laptop turned offf automatically, and you have to wait even 1 day to use it again. Finally I reburn the motherbord 1 time, change the video card 1 time and after spending 350 dollars I trow that laptop to trash.Honestly, I have used 2 HP laptops, the DV9000 and the DV2000, both have been a headache for me, bur specially the dv900, and maybe HP has some good producto, personally ill never buy another hewlett packard product again, in resume of the problems...horrible architectonical designbad prossesor decision on the AMD prosessorlame fan disposition for the video card, ram and prosessorand the custome servide (in Guatemala) was usseles.

Reviews.Title: HP PAVILION DV 6000 AND DV 9000
Reviews.Author: LEON CASTILLO "JOVEN"
Reviews.Content: I HAVE BOTH THE DV 6000 AND DV 9000.  MY DV 6000 I HAVE OWNED FOR FIVE YEARS AND I HAVE NEVER HAD THOSE PROBLEMS.  WHEN MY WIFE WANTED A NEW LAP TOP FOR HER SELF, I DID NOT THINK OF ANY THING EALSE OTHER THAN HP.  I HAVE HAD OTHER BRANDS PRIOR TO MY HP's.  I HAVE ALWAYS DONE MY RESEARCH AND COMPARISSON BEFORE I BUY.  HP LAP TOPs FOR ME ARE SECOND TO NONE.  I DO NOT LIKE TO BE ONE OF THOSE TEACHERS THAT WALKS AROUND SCHOOL WITH A LAP TOP WITH A PICTURE OF A FRUIT JUST TO IMPRESS EVERYONE; ALL THAT DOES IS TELL PEOPLE YOU ARE A BIG SPENDER AND NOT TOO WISE WITH YOUR MONEY.

Reviews.Title: Crashed after 2 years
Reviews.Author: Arun P. Arangil "arunap"
Reviews.Content: The laptop worked fine for 2 years before it crashed (It turns on then switches off after a few secs continuously). After i took it to the technicians they told me that the graphics card has issues and cant be repaired. They told me that the HP Pavilions (the dv series) has issues with nvidia graphics chip integration with the motherboard. Now i am trying to salvage the parts. I will never buy HP laptops again PERIOD.
